Path: backend/migrations/README.md
     1	# Database Migrations
     2	
     3	This directory contains database migration scripts for the Shans System.
     4	
     5	## Running Migrations
     6	
     7	To run all migrations, use the following command from the backend directory:
     8	
     9	```bash
    10	npm run migrate
    11	```
    12	
    13	This will execute all migration scripts in alphabetical order.
    14	
    15	## Available Migrations
    16	
    17	- `add_categories_table.js` - Creates the categories table and populates it with default categories.
    18	
    19	## Creating New Migrations
    20	
    21	When creating a new migration:
    22	
    23	1. Create a new JavaScript file in this directory with a descriptive name
    24	2. Follow the pattern in existing migrations
    25	3. Make sure to handle the case where the migration has already been applied
    26	4. Add error handling and logging
    27	
    28	Example structure:
